*************************************************
*	PENCILBENCH VER 0.1             	*
*************************************************

Set of Benchmarking Programs for 
Platform Neutral Compute Intermediate Language 
(PENCIL)

-------------------------------------------------
- Requirements 
	- Pencilcc
-------------------------------------------------

- Command to run benchmarks :

	- pencilcc <INCLUDE_PATH_IF_REQD> FILENAME/S ../utilities/include/pencilbench.c -o outfile
	- ./outfile

- You can find template for writing benchmarks at ./utilities

- It is also nice idea to compare sequential/ parallel execution. 	

- You can select dataset size by providing -D<DATA_SET_OPTION>
  Where DATA_SET_OPTION from : 	
	MINI_DATASET
	SMALL_DATASET
	STANDARD_DATASET (Default)
	LARGE_DATASET
	EXTRALARGE_DATASET

- Sample output for gemm benchmark :

	$./test 

 	Problem Size : 
 	RowA = 2500, ColA = 2500, ColB : 2500
 	Kernel Start
 	kernel end
 	Execution time :10.814283 
	
- .c = C code with possibly PENCIL code embedded.
  .pencil.c = <Only> PENCIL code. 

- Contributors
	- IIT-H Compiler Group
									
